Folwarki  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Stopnica, within Busko County, Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, in south-central Poland. It lies approximately  north of Stopnica,  east of Busko-Zdrój, and  south-east of the regional capital Kielce.
